<Base
  title="Clara by Meish — Guest Signal System"
  description="Clara helps the hotel hear the guest before the guest arrives, turning guest questions into a staff-facing Guest Signal Digest. Clara suggests; humans decide."
>
  <section class="section container">
    <p class="eyebrow">Hotels &amp; events · Pre-arrival</p>
    <h1>Clara helps the hotel hear the guest before the guest arrives.</h1>
    <p class="lead">Clara is a Guest Signal System for hotels and events. Before arrival,
      guests answer a few practical questions — parking, arrival, breakfast, accessibility,
      and how they'd like the stay to feel. Clara turns that into a clear, staff-facing digest.</p>

    <h2>How it works</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Guest shares</strong> — a short, warm pre-arrival conversation, not a form wall.</li>
      <li><strong>Clara translates</strong> — answers become a Guest Signal Digest your team can act on.</li>
      <li><strong>Staff decide</strong> — Clara suggests; humans approve and act (Human Approval Layer).</li>
      <li><strong>Nobody asks twice</strong> — information travels with the guest (No Repeating Protocol).</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Why hotels use it</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Turn guest questions into hotel intelligence</li>
      <li>Reduce repetitive front-desk load — less asking, more anticipating</li>
      <li>Fewer surprises at check-in; more moments that feel personal</li>
      <li>Staff-friendly by design — Clara lightens the workload, it doesn't watch the staff</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Where Clara is now</h2>
    <p>Piloting with events and meetings first; ordinary hotel-guest flow follows. Clara is a
      service presence for hotels and events — not a general chatbot, and not staff surveillance
      (<a href="/privacy">boundaries</a>).</p>

    <p><a class="button button--primary" href="/contact">Pilot Clara for your next event</a></p>
  </section>
</Base>
